<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Taiwan Authorities Urged to Respond to China's Appeal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Taiwan compatriots feel
disappointed at Taiwan Authorities' failure to respond to
President Jiang Zemin's appeal for holding cross-straits political
negotiations at an early date.
</P>
<P>
The remarks were made by Yang Guoqing, president of the
All-China Federation of Taiwan Compatriots, who is attending the
Ninth National People's Congress in session here since last
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The key factor to developing relations across the Taiwan
straits is to officially put an end to the state of hostility in
accordance with the principle that there is only one China and
hold political negotiations at an early date, he said.
</P>
<P>
All previous economic and business routine talks have been
halted by political issues, which worried Taiwan compatriots, said
the 62-year-old, Taiwan-born Yang, who came to China in the
capacity of a Chinese with Taiwan origin residing in Japan in
1953.
</P>
<P>
Yang's view was shared by other NPC deputies of Taiwan origin.
</P>
<P>
Liu Yiming, vice-chairman of the Central Committee of the
Taiwan Democratic Self-Government League, said that he, too, was
disappointed at the lack of sincerity by Taiwan authorities on
bilateral political negotiation.
</P>
<P>
Yang said, "I understand the feelings of Taiwan compatriots
who are longing for stability and peace. The principle of "One
country, two systems" is the best option for the solution of
Taiwan issue," he added.
</P>
<P>
He appealed to Taiwan authorities to take into account the
reiteration made by Premier Li Peng in his government report to
the NPC current session.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
