<BODY>
<HEADLINE> McLaren Not to Be Punished </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 9 (Xinhua) -- The McLaren team will not be
punished by the International Automobile Federation (FIA) over the
way Dave Coulthard allowed his teammate Mika Hakkinen to overtake
him and win Sunday's Australian Grand Prix in Melbourne.
</P>
<P>
FIA's decision on Monday followed a formal complaint by
organisers of the Australian race, according to the FIA.
</P>
<P>
The FIA said in a statement that "team orders" specifying the
finishing order of drivers within a team had existed in motor
sport since the beginning of the century.
</P>
<P>
It would therefore not be right to criticise or sanction
Mclaren for what it did at Sunday's grand prix, said the
statement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
