<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPPCC First Session Receives Record Number of Proposals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 9 (Xinhua) -- The First Session of the Ninth
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) had received 2,863 proposal by five o'clock
this afternoon, the deadline for proposal submission, a record in
the history of this top advisory body in China.
</P>
<P>
According to official sources, proposals on economic matters
such as economic planning, urban and rural development, transport
and telecommunications, finance, agriculture and forestry
outnumber all other proposals.
</P>
<P>
The proposals also concern: reform of state-owned enterprises,
re-employment of laid-off workers, prevention of financial risks,
environmental protection, accelerating development of non-public
and private economies, improvement of the legal system and
scientific and technological advances. 
</P>
</TEXT>
