<HEADLINE> Russian Premier Leaves for U.S. Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 9 (Xinhua) -- The United States has for the first
time become the leading investor in Russia, Russian Prime Minister
Viktor Chernomyrdin said before departing for his U.S. visit,
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin said his four-day visit will mainly deal with
economic issues. He is expected to meet U.S. President Bill
Clinton and Vice President Albert Gore and attend the 10th session
of the Russian-U.S. Commission for Economic and Trade Cooperation,
said the Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
The Russian premier said the trade volume between the two
countries stood at about eight billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin also denied again that Russia had transferred
missile or nuclear technologies to Iran or to any other country.
</P>
<P>
"Russia has not transferred and shall not transfer (either
missile or nuclear technologies) anything to Iran or other
countries," the prime minister said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
