<HEADLINE> Congress President Sitaram Kesri Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 9 (Xinhua) -- In a dramatic development,
Congress President Sitaram Kesri Monday announced his decision to
resign as the Congress president.
</P>
<P>
He said in a press conference here he said he had taken the
step in view of the developments in the past two months. "Have you
not seen how things took shape during the last two months? No man
with self-respect could tolerate this," he said.
</P>
<P>
The last two months has seen frequent references by the party's
star campaigner and widow of former Prime Minister Sonia Gandhi
that the party " needed a right leadership to make it strong and
vibrant".
</P>
<P>
He made a veiled attack on Sonia Gandhi at the press
conference, but he did not elaborate on it. He said that he would
convene a meeting of the Congress Working Committee (CWC), the
highest policy-making body of the party, Tuesday to decide the
date for the election of the Congress Parliamentary Party (CPP)
and he made it clear that he was not a candidate for the CPP
leadership.
</P>
<P>
83-year-old Kesri was elected the Congress president on June 9
last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
