<HEADLINE> Iraq Praises Arabs' Position Towards Baghdad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister Tariq
Aziz on Monday commended Arab world's popular and official
position toward his country which suffers from the seven-year-old
U.N. sanctions.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting with a visiting Yemeni delegation, Aziz described
as important and positive Arabs' support to Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The Yemeni delegation is led by member of Yemeni Consultative
Council and head of Red Crescent Society Saeed al-Hakeemi, the
Iraqi News Agency reported. The delegation brought a planeload of
medicine to Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Aziz praised Yemen's support of Iraq's demands for lifting the
embargo imposed on its people.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations imposed the sanctions on Iraq after it
invaded Kuwait in 1990.
</P>
<P>
For his part, al-Hakeemi expressed happiness that Iraq did
succeed to resolve the recent crisis with the United Nations over
weapons inspection.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi people is brave and has endured so much, said
al-Hakeemi, stressing that all Arab countries are with Iraqi
people, he said.
</P>
<P>
Al-Hakeemi called for the immediate and comprehensive lifting
of the embargo imposed on Iraq.
</P>
</TEXT>
