<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, March 9 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON -- Foreign ministers from the Contact Group on former
Yugoslavia opened talks on the Kosovo crisis Monday morning in
London amid worsening tensions in the Serbian Republic of
Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Ministers from the six-nation Contact Group, comprising the
United States, Russia, Britain, France, Germany and Italy, will
discuss possible international mediation in the crisis, ways of
preventing the conflict from spreading to neighboring countries
and diplomatic measures to urge Yugoslavia to solve the crisis
peacefully. (UK-Contact Group-Meeting)
</P>
