<BODY>
<HEADLINE> BIS: Asia Crisis By-Passes Some Currencies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Currencies in Latin American and
East European countries in the fourth quarter of 1997 were little
affected by the Asia economic crisis, a bank said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Basle-based Bank for International Settlements (BIS) also
said that equity indices in North America and Europe rapidly
recouped their losses.
</P>
<P>
The risk premium on Latin American and Eastern European
countries' foreign currency securities quickly retreated from
their late October peak, according to the BIS.
</P>
<P>
The subdued pace of securities issues in the second half of the
quarter reflected borrowers' willingness to delay issue in
anticipation of improved conditions as much as outright rationing
by international investors, the BIS said.
</P>
<P>
The bank noted that this view was supported by the fact that
issues launched by highly rated borrowers found a very favorable
market reception.
</P>
<P>
In the absence of improvements in external financial indicators
in many of these countries, the BIS believed that questions could
be raised over lessons drawn from the recent events. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
