<HEADLINE> Pak-Sri Lankan Relations Satisfactory: Ministers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Sri Lankan Minister of
Energy, Anuruddha Ratwatte, called on Minister for Water and Power
of Pakistan, Raja Nadir Pervaiz, here Monday. The two expressed
satisfaction with the existing close relations between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers exchanged views on matters of bilateral
interest with particular reference to power generation and
irrigation system, according to the Associated Press of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Both sides also hoped that the two countries could benefit from
each other's experience in the energy sector.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Monday, Anuruddha Ratwatte, who is also Deputy Minister
for Defense of Sri Lanka, called on Pakistan's Secretary Defense,
Iftikhar Ali Khan.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting Iftikhar hoped the excellent relations at
the military level between the two countries would continue to
flourish.
</P>
<P>
Anuruddha Ratwatte said that his country looks forward to
strengthening cooperation in all fields with Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Anuruddha Ratwatte arrived here Saturday. 
</P>
