<HEADLINE> S. African Police Make Biggest Drug Haul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Members of the South African Narcotics Bureau found the drugs in
the wooden crates of a consignment of welding equipment from Sao
Paulo, Brazil, during routine checks on inbound freight.
</P>
<P>
The cocaine, estimated at about 8.2 million Rand (1.65 million U.S.
dollars), is the largest amount seized in the country's airports,
South Africa Press Association reported.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of the year, police have foiled attempts to
smuggle more than 40 kilogram of cocaine through Johannesburg airport.
</P>
