<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Earth Tremor Hits Cyprus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, March 9 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.2 on
the Richter Scale hit Cyprus Monday afternoon, but no injuries or
damages were reported, according to Cyprus News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted Kyriacos Solomis of the Geological Survey
Department as saying that the quake occurred shortly after 1300
local time (1100 GMT), with the epicenter pinpointed at some 230
kilometers northwest of Paphos, in the sea area between Cyprus and
the Greek island of Rhodes.
</P>
<P>
The tremor lasted about ten seconds.
</P>
<P>
In 1996 an earthquake measuring 6.1 on the Richter Scale hit
the island. Around 50 people were slightly injured and many houses
in Limassol and Paphos were damaged.
</P>
<P>
A total of 67 people were killed in earthquakes in the past 100
years in Cyprus, which is situated in the second major seismic
zone in the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
