<HEADLINE> Tanzanian MP's Call for Investigating Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 9 (Xinhua) - The speaker of the Tanzanian
National Assembly (parliament) rejected Monday the request by a
group of members of the Assembly to summon the Legal and
Constitution Committee to probe the recent police killing of
unarmed citizens.
</P>
<P>
Speaker of parliament Pius Msekwa said in a statement that
there is no evidence to show that the Constitution was violated
as was accused in the MPs appealing letter and no special
committee can act on a matter which is still in the court.
</P>
<P>
He said that the proposed investigation was also limited by
the financial ability of parliament.
</P>
<P>
