system which means that the government expenditure is only for
the allocated amount each month," he added.
</P>
<P>
Late last week, MP Idrissa Msabaha, supported by the signature
of his 22 colleagues in parliament requested Pius Msekwa to
investigate the recent acts by the armed police against unarmed
citizens, with some causing deaths in Kigoma, Morogoro,
Kilimanjaro, Arusha, Mbeya and Dar es Salaam regions.
</P>
<P>
He demanded a meeting to be convened before the next
parliamentary session scheduled for April in Dodoma to verify
whether the police killings could be avoided.
</P>
<P>
On February 13, police opened fire on a rioting group near a
downtown mosque in Dar es Salaam, killing two people in the first
bloody and large-scale confrontation between police and citizens
since Tanzania's independence in 1961.
</P>
<P>
In northern Arusha region, police reportedly killed six
suspected bandits also in February. 
