<HEADLINE> French Language Compulsory in Nigerian Schools </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, March 9 (Xinhua) -- French language will become a compulsory
subject in Nigeria's junior secondary schools next
year, the official News Agency of Nigeria reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a meeting of principals and exmination officers at the
weekend in Minna, Professor Dibu Ojerinde, the registrar of the
National Board for Educational Measurement said the decision has been
taken by the National Council of Education.
</P>
