the language, due to the lack of teachers, inadequate textbooks as
well as cultural and religious barriers.
</P>
<P>
The idea of making French as the second official language has been
advocated by Nigerian Head of State General Sani Abacha, saying that
it is a necessary step to strengthen Nigeria's ties with many of its
French-speaking neighbors.
</P>
<P>
The idea may also has to do with the fact that France has been
taking a more flexible position towards the military government of
Abacha, than many of its west partners. 
