<HEADLINE> France Satisfied with Contact Group Approach to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 9 (Xinhua) -- France is satisfied with the
approach adopted by the six-nation Contact Group on former
Yugoslavia in London on Monday toward the crisis in the Yugoslav
province of Kosovo, said French Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Anne
Gazeau-Secret.
</P>
<P>
"It is the French approach which has prevailed," said
Gazeau-Secret when she was asked to comment on the outcome of the
meeting of foreign ministers of Britain, France, the United
States, Russia, Italy and Germany.
</P>
<P>
The Contact Group urged both the Yugoslav government and ethnic
Albanians in Kosovo to resolve their disputes through peaceful
dialogue, and condemned both the Serbian security forces and
"Kosovo Liberation Army" for their violent actions.
</P>
<P>
The spokeswoman praised the member countries of the Contact
Group for preserving their unity, because the endorsement of the
whole text of measures by Russia "gives more weight to the
message sent to (Yugoslav President) Milosevic."
</P>
<P>
She said that the measures taken by the Contact Group are
balanced because they let Belgrade "clearly catch a glimpse of "
the perspective of its reintegration into the international
community.
</P>
<P>
The spokeswoman also praised the Contact Group for condemning
terrorism and calling on countries concerned not to support
terrorism through arms supply.
</P>
<P>
"There is a unanimity of the countries of the Contact Group on
the principle of respecting the territorial integrity of the
Federal Republic of Yugoslavia and on the fact that the group is
neither in favor of independence of Kosovo, nor the status quo,
but wants a status of autonomy for this region (Kosovo)," she
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
