<DOCNO> XIE19980310.0085 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ninth NPC First Session Adopts Election, Appointment Method (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President and vice-president of the PRC, chairman of the
Central Military Commission, president of the Supreme People's
Court and procurator-general of the Supreme People's Procuratorate
are elected by way of one-candidate-for-one-post.
</P>
<P>
Election and appointment are carried out through secret
balloting, according to the methods.
</P>
<P>
In the course of election, if a certain candidate for chairman,
vice-chairmen or secretary-general of the NPC Standing Committee,
president and vice-president of the PRC, chairman of the Central
Military Commission, president of the Supreme People's Court and
procurator-general of the Supreme People's Procuratorate fails to
obtain over half the votes from all deputies, the presidium will
set forth a new nominee and another election is held.
</P>
<P>
In deciding upon the appointment of the members of the State
Council and vice-chairmen and members of the Central Military
Commission, if a nominee fails to get over half the votes from all
deputies, a new candidate, too, be nominated and another
election be held. If the new nominee again fails to obtain over
half the votes from all deputies, the appointment will be
suspended.
</P>
<P>
After the First Session is over, another new nominee will be
nominated. The nominees for vice-premiers and state councillors
will be submitted to the Second Session of the Ninth NPC for
appointment. The nominees for other posts will be submitted to the
Second Session of the Ninth NPC or the Ninth NPC Standing
Committee for appointment.
</P>
<P>
In the course of election and appointment, computers will be
used to count ballots, and consuled sites will be designated to
cast ballots.
</P>
<P>
The session will have 34 scrutineers, with a scrutineer
elected from each delegation and the scrutineer general. The list
of scrutineer-general and scrutineers will be submitted by the
presidium to the session for approval.
</P>
<P>
Led by the presidium, the scrutineer-general and scrutineers
supervise ballot distribution, voting process and ballot counting.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980310.0086 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Job-Creation Contest Approaches Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Ten projects have been chosen
from 85 entries as the European Union job-creation challenge
enters its final stage.
</P>
<P>
The shortlist of the job-creation projects in the competition
was announced on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Two of the finalists were from Britain, two from the
Netherlands and the remainder with one each from Spain, Italy,
France, Belgium, Germany and Finland.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission launched the contest last June with the
challenge focused on durable job-creation schemes in declining
industrial areas.
</P>
<P>
The shortlist was made with consideration of the schemes'
impacts on employment, originality, transferability and prospects
in long-term unemployment.
</P>
<P>
The finalist schemes are scheduled to be presented to the
European Job Challenge Seminar, which is to be held in Brussels on
April 29 and 30.
</P>
<P>
The competition, the first of its kind, was open to all
job-creation projects in effect since 1989 which were supported by
either the European Regional Development Fund or the European
Social Fund. 
</P>
</TEXT>
