<TEXT>
<P>
BIRMINGHAM, ENGLAND, March 10 (Xinhua) -- The International
Badminton Federation (IBF) has confirmed that the Thomas &AMP; Uber
Cup Finals will go ahead in Hongkong as planned on 15-24 May 1998.
</P>
<P>
Together with its commercial partners, the Federation has been
investigating new lines of funding and sponsorship from a variety
of sources, according to an announcement here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
These have proved encouraging and the Federation is confident
that deals can be arranged which will cover the cost of both the
Finals and the preliminary stages.
</P>
<P>
The financial difficulties in Southeast Asia have had other
repercussion. IBF had considered postponing the Thomas &AMP; Uber
Finals but the new developments have made this unnecessary.
</P>
<P>
Datuk Punch Gunalan, IBF Vice-President stressed the importance
of a successful launch for this elite series of seven tournaments,
four of which are planned for Southeast and East Asia.
</P>
<P>
"We want to give the best possible value to sponsors. As
several of the seven countries are under severe economic pressure,
it makes sense to reschedule," he added.
</P>
<P>
Lu Shengrong, IBF President, is confident that the current
problems are only a temporary setback. "By the beginning of the
year of badminton's third Olympics in Sydney, the sport expects to
be well and truly back on track," she said.  
</P>
