<HEADLINE> India Carries Out Terrorist Activities in Pakistan: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Information Minister
Mushahid Hussain Tuesday called on the world community to take
note of India's interference in his country's internal affairs by
carrying out terrorist activities in the country.
</P>
<P>
"We appeal to the international community to take note of these
developments which are taking innocent lives, damaging property
and attempting to destablize Pakistan," said Hussain at a press
conference held here Tuesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
"India's involvement in terrorism is threat to peace, security
and stability of South Asia," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that Pakistan's security agencies have collected
conclusive evidence proving that India was behind recent series of
bomb blasts.
</P>
<P>
The blasts were "carried out in a consistent pattern
--detonated either on bus stands or on railway platforms" through
its intelligence agency Research and Analysis Wing, he added.
</P>
<P>
Hussain further said that the terrorism perpetrated by New
Delhi in Pakistan "is aimed at destablizing a neighboring country
having a strong government unlike India and reflecting attention
from its prevailing political uncertainty."
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he said India wants to hoodwink the international
community by deflecting its attention from the troubles caused by
popular, spontaneous and indigenous uprising in held Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
Responding to a question, Hussain said some suspects have been
arrested in connection with recent bomb blasts.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he termed New Delhi's allegations that Pakistan was
behind bomb blasts in India as "baseless and false."
</P>
<P>
Three bomb blasts occurred in Pakistan in the last two days, in
which 15 people were killed and 82 injured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
