<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Host Int'l Ice Hockey Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 10 (Xinhua) -- An international ice hockey
tournament named Nortel World Ice Hockey Five-a-side Hong Kong '98
is to be held from March 12-15, it was announced on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Taking part in the four-day tournament, the first ever of its
kind since the establishment of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) last July, are 24 teams, seven more
than last year's field, from Beijing, Calgary, Dubai, Macao,
Prague, Singapore, Taipei, Tokyo and Toronto.
</P>
<P>
The tournament is to be held in two stages. The 12
participating teams of the men's division will play round-robin
matches in the three pools of four to establish the 1st to 12th
seeds. The top six seeds will play for the Nortel Championship
Trophy and the seventh to 12th seeds will compete for the
Budweiser Cup.
</P>
<P>
The seven sides in the Asian men's division will compete in a
double knock-out format to decide the winners.
</P>
<P>
And two local women's teams will compete against teams from the
University of Tsukuba (Japan), Calgary, Canada and Mega Wingers,
Manila for the top honors of the division. 
</P>
</TEXT>
