<HEADLINE> Bonded Zone In Eastern Chinese City Thriving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 10 (Xinhua) -- The Ningbo Bonded Zone in
the coastal city of Ningbo in Zhejiang Province has had rapid
development after five years of construction and 1.2 billion yuan
in spending on infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
It is the only zone of its kind in the province and mainly
handles international trade, export-oriented processing, and
bonded storage services.
</P>
<P>
It now has 2,100 enterprises, with registered capital of 1.2
billion US dollars, 331 of them overseas-funded, involving 488
million US dollars in total investment.
</P>
<P>
A 200,000-square-meter hi-tech park is taking shape in the
zone, where 30 export-oriented processing plants have gone into
operation.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the bonded zone had 1.3 billion yuan in GDP and 630
million US dollars in foreign trade, accounting for 19 percent of
the city's total. 
</P>
</TEXT>
