<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania to Join EU Environment Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Romania is to participate in the
European Union (EU) environment program apparently in an effort
toward being accepted for future membership of the leading
European organization.
</P>
<P>
It is the first east European country to declare its
intention to join the program known as LIFE, which is the EU's
financial instrument for the environment, European Commission
officials said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Romania's annual contribution to the program will be 2.2
million European Currency Units for the year 1998 and 1999.
</P>
<P>
The country will take other necessary steps to ensure national
coordination and organization in implementing the EU program.
</P>
<P>
The EU Luxembourg summit last December stressed the importance
of participation by applicant countries in EU programs as a key
issue of pre-accession strategy.
</P>
<P>
The Europe Agreements, signed between the EU and all candidate
countries, asks the associated countries to take part in EU
programs and indicates environment as an eligible area.
</P>
<P>
Applicant countries' participation in EU programs may be partly
financed by up to 10 percent of their Phare national allocation
funds.
</P>
<P>
Phare is an EU aid program directed to central and eastern
Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
