<HEADLINE> Qatari Emir to Visit Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Qatar's Emir Sheikh Hamad Bin
Khalifa al-Thani will visit Egypt to improve the bilateral
relations, the official Qatari News Agency (QNA) reported on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The emir "has accepted (Egyptian) President (Hosni) Mubarak's
invitation and is likely to visit Egypt," QNA quoted Fawaz al
Attiyah, Qatari Foreign Ministry spokesman, as saying.
</P>
<P>
The invitation was delivered by Egyptian Minister of Education
Hussein Kamel Bahauddin during a trip to Doha last week.
</P>
<P>
Al Attiyah expected the visit will come after a meeting of the
foreign ministers of the Organization of the Islamic Conference
members due to be held in Doha on March 15-19, QNA said.
</P>
<P>
The Doha-Cairo ties soured after Egypt was accused to have a
hand in a coup attempt to topple the Qatari government in 1996,
which Egypt has denied.
</P>
<P>
The disputes were exacerbated when Egypt, among others,
boycotted the Middle East and North Africa Economic Conference
Qatar hosted last December. 
</P>
</TEXT>
