<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier on Grain Production and Processing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng today
called for developing in-depth processing of grain and farm
produce to increase farmers' incomes and improve people's living
standard.
</P>
<P>
This will play a positive role in maintaining a stable and high
grain output in China and improving the efficiency of the
country's agriculture, Li said here today at a group discussion
attended by deputies to the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC)
from northeast China's Heilongjiang Province.
</P>
<P>
"Heilongjiang, one of China's leading grain producers, should
speed up the processing of its farm produce if it wants to become
an agricultural power," he said.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the difficulty to sell and store some kinds of
farm products is a temporary phenomenon. "There is a growing
demand for grain in China," the premier said.
</P>
<P>
"We should make every possible means to enhance the role of
agriculture as the economic base of the country, increase grain
production and develop grain processing to meet market needs," he
said.
</P>
<P>
The premier also called for developing border trade which he
said conforms to the strategy of diversifying China's foreign
trade.
</P>
<P>
He urged Heilongjiang to sum up experience in border trade,
build more export-oriented production bases and improve the
quality of its export goods.
</P>
<P>
The premier described Heilongjiang as a treasure house of
natural resources and spoke highly of its role in supplying the
nation with petroleum, grain, coal and timber. He urged the
province to improve infrastructures so as to fully tap its
economic potential.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
