<HEADLINE> Large Commercial Company Set Up In China's Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 10 (Xinhua) -- The Beifang International Group,
a large commercial company with 118 million US dollars worth of
registered capital and assets of 1.35 billion yuan, was set up
today in the city of Tianjin, a joint effort of state foreign
trade firms.
</P>
<P>
The group will deal with trade, finance, industry, and
information.
</P>
<P>
It consists of one core company and four others and owns 119
firms and companies at home and 17 overseas outlets and has trade
partners in more than 100 countries and regions. It is expected to
help local trade services and improve competitiveness both at home
and abroad.
</P>
<P>
The company plans to do 800 million US dollars worth of foreign
trade and have eight billion yuan in sales a year by the turn of
the century.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin also plans to build four to five similar enterprise
groups in the future to follow international development. 
</P>
