<DOCNO> XIE19980310.0117 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Institutional Restructuring Plan Submitted to Top Legislature (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 10 (Xinhua) -- The third plenum of the First
Session of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC) this
afternoon adopted the Decision on the Plan Concerning Institutional
Restructuring of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan, the following ministries and commissions
under the State Council will not be retained:
</P>
<P>
Ministry of Electric Power Industry, Ministry of Coal Industry,
Ministry of Metallurgical Industry, Ministry of Machine-building
Industry, Ministry of Electronics Industry, Ministry of Chemical
Industry, Ministry of Internal Trade, Ministry of Post and
Telecommunications, Ministry of Labor, Ministry of Radio, Film and
Television, Ministry of Geology and Mineral Resources, Ministry of
Forestry, State Physical Culture and Sports Commission, the
Commission of Science, Technology and Industry for National
Defense (CSTIND) [The new commission to be organized under the
same title will incorporate the national defense administrative
functions of the CSTIND, functions of the National Defense
Department of the former State Planning Commission, as well as the
government functions undertaken by various military industrial
corporations], and the State Commission for Restructuring the
Economy (the commission will be turned into a counselling body
headed concurrently by the premier and composed of relevant
ministers in a bid to increase the State Council's leaership over
the work of economic structural reform, and will not be listed
into the series of the component departments under the State
Council).
</P>
<P>
Three new ministries and commissions are planned to be
established:
</P>
<P>
The Commission of Science, Technology and Industry for National
Defense, Ministry of Information Technology and Telecom Industries,
Ministry of Labor and Social Security, and Ministry of Land and
Natural Resources.
</P>
<P>
Three ministries and commission are planned to be renamed:
</P>
<P>
The State Planning Commission will be renamed State Development
Planning Commission, the State Science and Technology Commission
will be renamed Ministry of Science and Technology, and the State
Education Commission will be renamed Ministry of Education.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
