<HEADLINE> Leipzig Trade Fair to Host China Days </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Leipzig will hold its first China
days, according to Thomos Gindele, a representative in Beijing, at
the International Trade Fair for Passenger Transport and Goods
Traffic, from May 6 to 9.
</P>
<P>
May 7 and 8 will be set aside for "China Days Transport and
Logistics", backed by the China Communication and Transportation
Association (CCTA), the German-Chinese Agency for Cooperation in
Communications and Transportation, and the Leipzig Fair.
</P>
<P>
China Days will be the core of the Fair, which is one of 18
regularly held international fairs, Gindele says.
</P>
<P>
Wang Derong, vice-president of CCTA, had said after the Munich
Fair's China Days last year that CCTA would help Chinese
businesses cooperate with European colleges for the second event,
in Leipzig.
</P>
<P>
The global economy and different ways to move goods on the
domestic market mean that China needs to improve the quality of
its transport and logistics, Wang said, expressing the hope that
China Days can help increase contacts with sectors in Germany and
other countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
