<DOCNO> XIE19980310.0127 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng on Township Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng today called on
the country's massive number of township enterprises to improve
management, step up technical innovation and take an active part
in international competition.
</P>
<P>
Li made the call in a group discussion with deputies from east
China's Zhejiang Province to the National People's Congress (NPC),
in session here since last Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that China's township enterprises are fairly highly
adaptable to market changes. A number of township enterprises,
despite having achieved a fair level of economies of scale from
manual operations, still need to adjust their product mix,
increase the "technology content" of their products and further
enhance their adaptability to the market, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said there are still a large number of labor-intensive
township enterprises in China. Greater efforts should be made to
sharpen the competitive edge of these enterprises to cope with
intensifying competition at home and abroad, he said.
</P>
<P>
On the foreign trade sector, Li said that, in addition to
improving product quality and taking appropriate measure to
promote exports, China should carry out reform of its foreign
trade system in greater depth and in a planned and systematic way.
</P>
<P>
The premier also called for reducing production cost and
exploring more markets overseas for Chinese products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
