<HEADLINE> Fixed Assets Investment Increases In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 10 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Capital invested 4.69
billion yuan in fixed assets during the first two months of the
year, a 68.5 percent rise from the same period in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Of that amount, 3.4 billion yuan came from the local
government, an 82.6 percent increase, and the remainder from
central government.
</P>
<P>
The fixed assets investment in capital construction and real
estate grew by 66.5 percent and 41.6 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
During the two-month period, construction of 176,000
square meters of floor space was completed, including 51,000
square meters of residential buildings. 
