<HEADLINE> Beijing Aviation Training Center's Flight Simulators Certified </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Two flight simulators at the
Beijing CASC-Airbus Training Center for the A320 series and the
A330/A340 obtained their certification from the Civil Aviation
Administration of China (CAAC) and France's Aviation
Administration, today.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Center, which is China's first aviation service
center to combine training and support, was set up by the China
Aviation Supplies Import and Export Corporation (CASC) and the
Airbus Industrie on May 17 last year.
</P>
<P>
Its simulators were given the highest level of certification,
which allows pilots to be approved for flight without further base
training, saving airlines time and money. They were manufactured
by France's Thomson CSF and are among the most advanced equipment
in the world.
</P>
<P>
The center is part of Airbus Industrie's global training
network and is the most advanced training facility of its kind in
China. It covers 8,000 square meters and is intended to help meet
the training needs of Airbus operators in China and the
Asia-Pacific region.  
</P>
