<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ramos Orders Investigation of Pyramid Scam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
Tuesday ordered the thorough investigation of a millions-of-pesos
pyramid scam whose victims include the wife and daughter of Vice
President Joseph Estrada.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said the National Bureau of Investigation will be the
lead agency to look into the scam allegedly masterminded by
Josephine German, wife of Estrada's public relations consultant
Aurelio Reli German.
</P>
<P>
The president ordered the agency to find out how Josephine
German managed to defraud at least 20 people of 800 million pesos
(20 million U.S. dollars) without being unmasked sooner.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Ramos called on the victims to cooperate by
providing vital information to the probers so that they can get to
the bottom of the case.
</P>
<P>
Josephine German reportedly started her business in 1989 by
asking people to invest while assuring them of high interests in a
very short period of time.
</P>
<P>
Her business went big time last year when she began inviting
rich and prominent people to invest millions of pesos. However,
she started having problems with the business during the first
week of February this year and then fled abroad.
</P>
<P>
Estrada had asked the Department of Foreign Affairs to cancel
the passport of the suspect and sought her deportation.
</P>
<P>
Ramos declined to make any conclusion pending the result of the
investigation, saying he does not want to make any conclusions at
this stage "because we do not have too many details about the
matter".
</P>
<P>
Estrada is the presidential candidate of the united opposition
in the May 11 elections. He has been the front-runner in most
popularity surveys on the presidentiables. 
</P>
</TEXT>
