<HEADLINE> Indian Intelligence Agency Involved in Terrorism in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan said Tuesday that it
had solid evidence to prove that the Indian Intelligence Agency,
Research and Analysis Wing, was involved in recent acts of
terrorism in the country.
</P>
<P>
"Conclusive evidence in possession of the government of
Pakistan clearly pots to the fact that these terrorist acts were
masterminded and executed by the Research and Analysis Wing," said
a Foreign Office spokesman in a press release issued Tuesday,
according to the Associated Press of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that recent bomb blasts in Pakistan, which
caused loss of innocent lives, "are a part of a well orchestrated
plan of terrorism."
</P>
<P>
"The latest replay of this abominable violence was in crowded
passenger trains where sophisticated time devices were used," the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He also said that "dastardly acts of violence have also been
carried out to ignite strain violence in Pakistan resulting in the
killing of foreigners."
</P>
<P>
"The perpetrators of these heinous crimes, who are obviously
trying to divert attention from the collapse of a system spawned
by successive weak governments, can never succeed in intimidating
the government and the people of Pakistan, nor dilute their
resolve to combat terrorism in all its forms," he added.
</P>
<P>
Such dastardly acts will only serve to vitiate the atmosphere
in a region that is already tense and volatile, the spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
Three bomb blasts took place in the last two days in Pakistan,
out of which two were in a passenger train. The incidents killed
15 people and injured 82. 
</P>
