<HEADLINE> American Coach to Name World Cup Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Steve Sampson, United States
national coach, will name the core of his World Cup squad this
month, according to a report from San Diego on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Countries have until June 2 to inform the game's governing body
FIFA of their official squad of 22 for the World Cup to be begun
in Paris on June 10.
</P>
<P>
But Sampson says he will privately notify 10-15 players they
will be going to France 98 to relieve them of the pressure.
</P>
<P>
"I think it's important to start giving certain individuals
confidence they are on the team," Sampson was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
"There is a high level of anxiety associated with making the
World Cup team. I want to relieve that."
</P>
<P>
One of the complaints players had with former coach Bora
Milutinovic was they never knew whether they would be picked or
not, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Chris Henderson, who played in the 1990 and 1994
World Cups, approved Sampson's decision.
</P>
<P>
American form has gone up and down recently. A high point was
the 1-0 win over world champions Brazil but that was followed by
defeats to Mexico 0-1, the Netherlands 0-2 and Belgium 0-2.
</P>
<P>
England-based goalkeepers Kasey Keller and Brad Fielder,
strikers Eric Winalda and Ernie Stewart, midfielders John Harkes,
Claudio Reyna and Preki Radosavljevic, and defenders Eddie Pope,
Marcelo Balboa and Thomas Dooley all look likely to make Sampson's
first choice.
</P>
<P>
The USA has been drawn in Group F with Germany, Yugoslavia and
Iran. 
</P>
</TEXT>
