<HEADLINE> Foreign Ministry Says Taiwan Using Financial Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry
Spokesman Zhu Bangzao today said Taiwan authorities are seeking
their own benefits by taking advantage of the Asian financial
crisis.
</P>
<P>
He said that Taiwan devalued the currency by 10 percent in
October, causing a slump in the stock markets of Hong Kong and
some Southeast Asian countries, worsening the financial turmoil in
the region.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that some Taiwanese politicians led a number of
business executives in carrying out activities to enhance
substantial relations with certain countries by committing
themselves to economic assistance or financial cooperation.
</P>
<P>
In taking advantage of the financial turmoil they have
demonstrated their selfishness, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated the "One China" policy of the Chinese government,
stressing that China does not oppose any non-government economic
and trade contacts between Taiwan and other countries.
</P>
<P>
But it resolutely opposes countries that have diplomatic
relations with China in making of official contacts of any form
with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese position has the understanding and support of many
countries and the attempt of the Taiwan authorities is doomed to
failure, Zhu said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
