<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Two teenagers from the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) will have their
long-standing dream come true as they will have the chance to be
on the actual playing field during this year's World Cup soccer
matches.
</P>
<P>
The two chosen from the special annual Coca-Cola Schools Soccer
Stars Parade campaign will, apart from learning soccer skills from
local football professionals, represent Hong Kong SAR at the World
Cup.
</P>
<P>
The Parade set for April 4 and 18 at the Hong Kong Sports
Institute, is running into the ninth consecutive year and is
expected to attract some 2,000 local youngsters, according to the
organizers.
</P>
<P>
The candidates will attend soccer clinics hosted by local
pro-players and go through rounds of challenges testing their
soccer skills and knowledge, aptitude and foreign language skills
to become SAR's "football ambassadors" to France.
</P>
<P>
They will serve as Flag Bearer and Ball Kid, it was announced
here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Flag Bearer will carry the flag of a competing country or
region in the stadium before a World Cup game and the Ball Kid
will assist referees during an actual match in retrieving balls.
</P>
<P>
The two selected Hong Kong SAR "ambassadors" will join more
than 1,600 young soccer fans from more than 60 countries and
regions in the world in June this year for the World Cup event
June 10 to July 12 in France. 
