<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tourist Arrivals Rising in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Tourist arrivals in Macao rose by
6.6 percent in January this year, reversing the declining trend of
last year.
</P>
<P>
The latest figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics
Department on Tuesday show that visitor arrivals reached 621,334
in January, up 6.6 percent from the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
The increase was due mainly to Hong Kong visitors, whose
number surged by 37.3 percent. Tourist arrivals from the Republic
of Korea, Japan, Taiwan, Southeast Asian nations, Australia and
Europe all dropped sharply, by at least 30 percent.
</P>
<P>
Macao received some 7 million tourists last year, down 14
percent from 1996. The decline was blamed as the mixed result of a
wide coverage of Macao crime rates, the financial crisis in
Southeast Asia and fewer visitors from Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Tourism contributes about 40 percent of tax revenues of the
government of Macao, which is known for its Oriental casinos and
South European-style buildings. Its annual international music
festival and Formula 3 Grand Prix are also major attractions.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980310.0154 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin on Army Building (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the face of new circumstances, Jiang said, the Party Central
Committee and the CMC have set forth new strategic principles for
military development, and have stressed the importance of
improving army strength with science and technology.
</P>
<P>
The new principles aim at enabling the Chinese army to win
victories in local wars that are fought with modern technologies,
especially with high-technologies, and place emphasis on the
quality rather than the quantity of troops, he explained.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, the modernization of national defense and the
army is a long-term historical task that requires constant efforts
of several generations.
</P>
<P>
"We must take Deng Xiaoping Theory as our guidance and study
the characteristics and laws of national defense and army building
under new circumstances in a down-to-earth manner, to further
improve our work," he noted.
</P>
<P>
It's also very important to correctly handle the relationship
between economic development and the building of national defense,
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"Building a modernized army and national defense is a guarantee
for the country's safety and modernization drive. But without a
highly developed economy, it's also impossible to promote the
modernization of national defense and the army," Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
"We must always insist on taking economic development as the
central task while paying adequate attention to modernizing
national defense, and seek a coordinated development for both the
economy and national defense," he said.
</P>
<P>
Unremitting efforts should be made to promote the style of hard
work and plain living in the whole army, to improve the ability of
officers and soldiers to resist the corrosive influence of any
decadent ideology and culture, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"Leading officers must play an exemplary role in promoting
frugality and thrift and opposing extravagance and waste. This is
by no means a trivial matter, but a major political issue
concerning the morale of the Party and the army and the success or
failure of our cause," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Jiang told the army deputies that this year China would make
greater efforts to combat corruption and build a clean Party and
government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
