<HEADLINE> Macao Reports Progress in Civil Service Localization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Government Information Office (GCS) said in a press release
on Tuesday that an overall of 87.56 percent of Macao's civil
service forces have been localized so far.
</P>
<P>
Among the local servants, some 20 percent are holders of higher
learning institution diplomas.
</P>
<P>
In a separate news release, the GCS said that among all civil
servants, the mother tongue of 78.17 percent is Chinese, 21.07
percent is Portuguese.
</P>
<P>
It said that 76.5 percent of leadership have been localized,
comparing with only about 30 percent at the end of 1995.
</P>
<P>
An important issue in the transitional period, the localization
of civil service is deemed vital for a smooth handover. The Macao
Government has promised to have all heads of departments basically
localized by the end of 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
