<HEADLINE> India, Sweden agree to Focus on Five Cooperation Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Swedish Ambassador to India K.
G. Engstrom said Tuesday that Sweden and India had agreed to focus
on five areas of cooperation in future.
</P>
<P>
The two countries would focus on poverty-oriented projects and
programs in the primary education and health sectors, environment
and energy. A consultancy fund would be set up and expertise
shared in various fields, he said at an Indo-Swedish workshop
here.
</P>
<P>
Scientists from both countries would discuss food processing,
environment and energy-related issues at the two-day workshop,
which started here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A new program, under the Department of Science and Technology
(DST), the Swedish International Development Cooperation Agency
and the Swedish Research Council for Engineering Sciences, would
involve short-duration projects of developmental relevance, said
DST adviser A. P. Kulshrestha.
</P>
<P>
More sectors including advanced materials, automation and
robotics and biotechnology would be explored by the two sides for
cooperation, once the mutual confidence builds up, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
