<HEADLINE> Plenary Meeting of Ninth NPC Session Hears Reports (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Major tasks for 1998 and a longer period to come are to
strengthen law enforement, reform courts and build contingents of
competent judges so as to provide a judicial guarantee for pushing
the socialist cause with Chinese characteristics into the 21st
century, Ren Jianxin said.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Siqing, procurator-general of the Supreme People's
Procuratorate, said that procuratorial bodies at all levels across
the country have played an active role in combating corruption,
severely cracking down on major crimes and safeguarding judicial
justice and a unified legal system.
</P>
<P>
From 1993 to 1997, he said, procuratorial bodies across the
country investigated 387,352 cases of power abuse, including
graft, bribery, dereliction of duty and infringement on citizens'
personal and democratic rights.
</P>
<P>
Procuratorate organs prosecuted 181,873 people for graft,
bribery and dereliction of duty.
</P>
<P>
"Investigations into these criminal cases, especially major
cases of great impact involving leading officials, show that the
struggle against corruption is going deeper," Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that in the next period, procuratorial bodies at all
levels will continue to make more efforts in the investigation and
punishment of power abuse cases, crack down on major criminal
offenses, improve supervision over law enforcement, train
contingents of highly competent and professional procurators, and
strive for the establishment of a socialist procuratorial system
with Chinese characteristics. 
