<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji Stresses Importance of Management Competence at State Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji today
emphasized the importance of a good management for state-owned
enterprises to get prosperous.
</P>
<P>
"Only by having a good management can state-owned enterprises
fundamentally improve their operational situation," said Zhu, also
a member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the
Chinese Communist Party Central Committee, in a group discussion
attended by deputies from Sichuan Province to the National
People's Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that supplies now exceed demand on the market,
indicating that "we've bid farewell to an economy of shortages."
</P>
<P>
"One the other hand," he said, "it shows that there have been
too many redundant construction projects."
</P>
<P>
"That is why it is high time we readjusted the industrial
structure and the product mix," he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhu noted that some state-owned enterprises have been heavily
debt-ridden and some have not been able to turn to profitability
for a long time.
</P>
<P>
"An important reason for this is that these enterprises do not
have a good group of executives," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Some executives do not feel guilty in the least when their
businesses are suffering great losses. How can such enterprises
change for the better with such people in charge?" he said.
</P>
<P>
"We cannot put an end to state-owned enterprises continuing to
lose money without solving the leadership problem in enterprises
and without changing the outdated management structure," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
