<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Procuratorial Bodies Play Active Role (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The procuratorial bodies have also earnestly fulfilled its duty
of supervision over law enforcement according to the Constitution
and laws on criminal, civil and administrative procedures, Zhang
said.
</P>
<P>
In their case examinations over the past years, procuratorial
bodies across China have prompted the arrest of 34,572 criminal
suspects originally neglected in case investigations, and
prosecuted 14,371 suspects that originally escaped prosecution.
</P>
<P>
They have also put forth 12,806 suggestions for the courts to
correct law violations in judicial proceedings, and contested
judgments in 12,288 cases they believed to be wrong.
</P>
<P>
In their supervision over the carrying out of sentences, the
procuratorial bodies have centered on fighting illegal activities
such as detentions exceeding legal time limit and violations of
the law in reducing criminals' prison terms and granting them
releases on parole.
</P>
<P>
According to the principle of seeking truth from facts and
correcting every mistake, they re-examined 47,590 criminal cases
upon appeal and made corrections in 4,285 cases according to law.
</P>
<P>
Zhang noted that in the past five years, procuratorial bodies
across the country have made active efforts to promote reform of
the judicial system and improve the procuratorial system.
</P>
<P>
These efforts include further improving the system of accepting
the supervision of people's congresses at all levels and their
standing committees, earnestly implementing the amended Criminal
Law and Criminal Procedure Law, intensifying efforts to probe into
cases of power abuse, reforming the traditional way of case
examination and prosecution, and improving the general quality and
law enforcement competence of the prosecutors.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that in the next period, procuratorial bodies at all
levels would continue to make major efforts in the investigation
and punishment of cases of power abuse, combat major criminal
offences, improve supervision over law enforcement, train a
contingent of highly competent and professional prosecutors, and
strive for the establishment of a socialist procuratorial system
with Chinese characteristics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
