<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
today urged the People's Liberation Army (PLA) to heighten its
sense of discipline, maintain a high degree of stability and
unity, and build a smaller but stronger army with science and
technology.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also general secretary of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) and chairman of the Central
Military Commission (CMC), made these remarks at a meeting of PLA
deputies to the Ninth National People's Congress, China's top
legislature, in session here since last Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"All officers and soldiers of the army must heighten their
sense of discipline, persistently subject themselves to the
command of the Party Central Committee and the CMC, and always
maintain a high degree of stability and unity of the troops, to
accomplish excellently various tasks given by the Party and the
people," Jiang told the deputies.
</P>
<P>
Party committees at all levels in the army should make
persistent efforts to arm the mind of officers and soldiers with
Deng Xiaoping Theory and guidelines of the 15th CPC National
Congress and carry out the Party's line, principles and policies
in an exemplary way, to provide an active support for the
country's various reforms and undertakings, said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
He also urged the whole army, especially leading officers at
all levels, to enhance their awareness of the overall situation,
treat correctly the adjustment of interests, and voluntarily
subject themselves to and serve the country's overall situation.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that due to the rapid development of high
and new technologies, major breakthroughs are in the works in
military circles of the modern world.
</P>
<P>
"As a global military reform keeps gaining momentum, military
powers in the world have one after another readjusted development
strategies for their armies, in a bid to speed up army
modernization and overtake other countries in army quality," Jiang
noted.
</P>
