<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 10 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan Navy confronted a
group of Tamil rebel boats Tuesday on the northeastern coast of
the island country and destroyed five of them including a large
one equipped with radar.
</P>
<P>
A flotilla of these boats was observed by naval patrol ships
while they were sailing from Mullaitivu to Trincomalee, the
evening newspaper Observer here said.
</P>
