<HEADLINE> Sino-Canadian Aero-Engine Company Formed in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Pratt and Whitney Canada (PWC)
and China National South Aero-Engine Company (SAEC) has announced
the formation of Southern Pratt and Whitney Aero-Engine Company
Ltd., which will manufacture gas turbine engine components for PWC.
</P>
<P>
The investment in the joint venture is more than 27 million
U.S. dollars. SAEC will have a 51 percent ownership share. The
joint venture will be located in Zhuzhou, a city in central
China's Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
SAEC, a company under the Aviation Industries of China (AVIC),
is the leading small gas-turbine engine manufacturer in the
country.
</P>
<P>
PWC, a world leader in the production of gas turbine engines
for utility aircraft, helicopters and regional/commuter markets,
as well as for industrial and marine applications, is a subsidiary
of United Technologies Corp. of the United States.
</P>
<P>
By joining forces, the SAEC/PWC partnership will promote the
development of China's aviation industry and actively participate
in one of the world's fastest growing civil aviation markets,
officials said.
</P>
<P>
This is the third joint venture between Pratt and Whitney and
engine factories under AVIC and the 20th joint company between
United Technologies divisions and Chinese partners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
