<HEADLINE> Cargo Ship Sinking in S. Africa, Crew Rescued </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 10 (Xinhua) -- A cargo ship, Golden Union,
is sinking off southeast coast of South Africa Tuesday morning,
but all 33 crew members on board have been rescued, South African
Press Association quoted South African Air Force as saying.
</P>
<P>
The ship, registered in Malta, was three-quarter full of water
by 6 a.m. (0400 GMT) Tuesday morning at rough seas about six
kilometers off Port St Johns.
</P>
<P>
The crew members were taken to Port St Johns and no one was
injured.
</P>
<P>
Two helicopters were dispatched from Durban, about 280
kilometers northeast of Port St Johns, shortly after distress
calls were received at about 4 a.m. (0200 GMT). They reached the
ship by about 7 a.m. (0500 GMT). 
</P>
