<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Funds Needed for Taihu Lake Cleanup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Monday's Shanghai-based "Wenhui Daily" quoted the survey as
saying that the water-quality turnaround will be achieved by 2010
and maintained for another decade.
</P>
<P>
The needed investment does not cover the input of local
enterprises to turn themselves into "clean production," which is
also expected to be a huge sum.
</P>
<P>
Even with such an investment, however, water quality in the
western part of the lake will deteriorate again by 2020 as economy
in the region grows rapidly.
</P>
<P>
It takes 5 to 15 years to pollute a lake, but 15 to 100 years
to restore it, according to the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The two-year survey has provided large amounts of information
on the general pollution situation in the Taihu Lake valleys.
</P>
<P>
The survey also covers the lake bed, for the first time
gathering information on pollution of the mud and its part in
contributing to the lake's over-nutrition.
</P>
<P>
China has approved the Plan for Preventing and Treating Water
Pollution of the Taihu Lake during the Ninth Five-Year Plan period
(1996-2000). All factories in the Taihu Lake area are required to
meet discharge standards this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
