<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Standing Committee Enhances Supervision on Law-enforcement (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Senior legislator Tian Jiyun said
here today that the Eighth NPC Standing Committee has, over the past
five years, gone on giving the same emphasis on the examination
and supervision over the law implementation as on law-making.
</P>
<P>
Through the examinations, various administrative departments,
courts and procuratorial organs have improved their work in
law-enforcement, laws are implemented better and the people have
become increasingly aware of laws, he said.
</P>
<P>
Tian, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the Eighth
National People's Congress (NPC), made remarks at the third
plenary meeting of the First Session of the Ninth NPC in his
report on the work of the Eighth NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, the Eighth NPC Standing Committee has
examined the implementation of 21 laws and decisions on the related
laws, and the special committees of the NPC have also conducted
examinations on the implementation of the relevant laws.
</P>
<P>
To safeguard the foundation of agriculture in the national
economy and promote the growth of agriculture and rural market
economy, the Standing Committee has examined the implementation of
Agriculture Law for consecutive years.
</P>
<P>
The Standing Committee has made arrangements on inspecting how
the Environmental Protection Law, Water Law, Forestry Law, and
other laws concerning environment and resources were implemented.
"Fairly Good results have been attained," he said.
</P>
<P>
In view of existing problems prevalent in the order of market
economy, the Standing Committee has examined, among other laws and
regulations, the implementation of Anti-Unfair Competition Law,
and the Law on the Protection of Consumers' Right and Interests,
</P>
<P>
These examinations have played a positive role in improving the
contingents of law-enforcement workers, overcoming protectionism
practiced in some areas and by some departments, and straightening
out the market order.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the NPC Standing Committee has examined the
implementation of more than 10 laws and decisions, including the
Law on Education and Law on Scientific and Technological Progress.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980310.0217 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Standing Committee Enhances Law-Enforcement Supervision (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the field of work supervision, a system in which the NPC
Standing Committee hears and deliberates the reports of the State
Council and its subsidiary departments, the Supreme People's Court
and the Supreme People's Procuratorate, has been formed.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, the Standing Committee has heard 34
work reports of the above-mentioned organs, which involved banking
business, foreign trade, education, building a clear and honest
government, agriculture, forestry, civil aviation, reform of large
and medium-sized state-owned enterprises, and alleviating farmers'
burdens.
</P>
<P>
Concerning the country's major reform measures and hot topics
about which the masses of people care, the reports have
contributed greatly to acquainting the Standing Committee with the
progress of reform, and supervising the reform and the
implementation of measures for development, Tian said.
</P>
<P>
Local people's congresses have, in recent years, pioneered some
effective ways of organizing deputies to assess the work of
governments, courts and procuratorates, appraise the performance
of officials whom the people's congress and its standing committee
have elected or decided to appoint.
</P>
<P>
In addition, local people's congresses and their standing
committees have urged relevant departments to set up the system in
which law-enforcing workers should held responsible for their own
work, and the system in which people responsible for causing cases
of misjudgment will be prosecuted.
</P>
<P>
"The Eighth NPC Standing Committee affirms such experience and
methods and supports local people's congresses to exercise their
supervisory power according to law," Tian Jiyun said.
</P>
<P>
He further noted that the Eighth NPC Standing Committee has
exerted great efforts to carry out the supervisory
responsibilities endowed by the Constitution. However, supervision
remains the weak points in the work of the NPC.
</P>
<P>
At present, the failure to abide by the law, laxity in law
enforcement, letting law-breakers go free, law-breaking by
law-enforcing personnel and acceptance of bribes remain severe in
some areas and departments.
</P>
<P>
"The masses of the people complain much about the problems and
ask the NPC and its Standing Committee to strengthen supervision,"
Tian Jiyun said.
</P>
<P>
The NPC Standing Committee should take more measures to further
improve and strengthen the examination and supervision over the
implementation of laws. The examination and supervision must be
more effective and formalism must be guarded against, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
