<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, March 10 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG -- The Sino-British Joint Liaison Group (JLG) will
hold its 42nd meeting in London on March 17-18, the Chinese side
of the JLG announced here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Attending the meeting on the Chinese side will be Chief
Representative Ambassador Wang Guisheng, Lu Ping, Secretary for
Constitutional Affairs of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region Michael Suen, Cheng Shousan, Vice-Director of the Hong
Kong-Macao Affairs Office of the Chinese Foreign Ministry Wang
Weiyang and related experts. (Hong Kong-JLG-Meeting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- At least nine people were killed and 35 others
injured Tuesday when a bomb went off in a passenger train in
Pakistan's eastern province of Punjab.
</P>
<P>
The explosion took place at 7:25 a.m. (local time). The train
was heading for Kasur, about 50 kilometers southeast of the
provincial capital of Lahore, the Associated Press of Pakistan
said. This was the second train blast in the past two days in the
province. A blast occurred Monday afternoon on a running train
near a small town named Wan Adhan, about 56 kilometers southwest
of Lahore, killing five people and injuring 35 others.
(Pakistan-Bomb Blast)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Soeharto was re-elected President of Indonesia
Tuesday for a fresh five-year term, making the retired general one
of the longest-serving heads of state in the world.
</P>
<P>
His re-election, a foregone conclusion, was agreed upon by the
1,000-member People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) without taking a
poll. "Since there was only one presidential candidate, he is
automatically formalized as president according to the law,"
Chairman of the Assembly Harmoko said at the 10th plenary session
of the MPR. (Indonesia-Soeharto) 
</P>
</TEXT>
