<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australia to Make Law on Foreign Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Australian Treasurer Peter
Costello said on Tuesday that legislation will be introduced this
week to allow the Australian government to provide billion-dollar
support packages to Indonesia and the Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
"Later on this week the government will be introducing
legislation to make good on Australia's commitment to
international financial packages in respect of (the Republic of)
Korea and Indonesia," Costello told the parliament.
</P>
<P>
Australia offered each of the two countries 1 billion U.S.
dollars last year as a backup loan facility to the IMF rescue
packages negotiated after the collapse of the Indonesian and South
Korean currencies.
</P>
<P>
Costello said Australia had been at the forefront of
international measures to respond to the emerging financial crisis
in East Asia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
