<DOCNO> XIE19980310.0228 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Construction of Water Conservation Project Going Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the largest water
conservation project on the Huaihe River is well on its way.
</P>
<P>
So far, 750 million yuan has been invested in building the
Huaihong New River project. A total of 87 million cubic meters of
earth and stones has been dug and a 210-kilometer-long embankment
and 50 accessory buildings have been completed.
</P>
<P>
The 125-meter-long new river will play an important role in
flood control along the Huaihe River, by discharging 2,000 cubic
meters of flood waters per second.
</P>
<P>
The project will also be used for irrigation, transportation
and aquatic products breeding.
</P>
<P>
With an investment of 1.4 billion yuan, the project started in
1991 and is expected to be completed in 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
