<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brunet, Myklebust Win More Golds in Paralympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Alexandre Brunet of France snatched
his second gold medal in the nordic cross country men's 10
kilometers sitski race in his debut Winter Paralympic Games in
Hakuba on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Ragnhild Myklebust of Norway won her third straight
gold medal in Nagano in the women's 5km sitski event.
</P>
<P>
Brunet's winning time was 37 minutes 13.9 seconds, more
than one minute faster than silver medallist Michail Terentiev of
Russia and bronze medallist Heinz Frei of Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Brunet was paralysed in his legs after crashing into a tree
during cross country practice in France just three years ago.
</P>
<P>
Myklebust, despite having a cold, dominated the difficult Snow
Harp course in Hakuba with a time of 19 minutes 19.9 seconds to
defeat Collette Bourgonje of Canada and Olena Akopyan of Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
Myklebust, now 54, also collected four gold medals in
Lillehammer four years ago and two each in 1992 and 1988, and she
is determined to quit the sport after Nagano to concentrate on
her work as a physiotherapist. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
