<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading S. African Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 10 (Xinhua) -- The following are major
news items in leading South African newspapers Tuesday:
</P>
<P>
The Citizen:
</P>
<P>
-- The South African police have seized 27.5 kilograms of
uncut cocaine, with an estimated street value of more than 8
million Rand (1.6 million U.S. Dollars), at Johannesburg
International Airport, the police announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Star:
</P>
<P>
-- A ruling on whether South African President Nelson Mandela
should testify in the Pretoria High Court for the rugby row, an
unprecedented move involving the head of state, will be made on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Business Day:
</P>
<P>
-- The South African Gold Crisis Committee, consisting of
senior government, labor, and business representatives, reached
agreement Monday on measures to reduce retrenchments at gold
mines. 
</P>
