<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese City Trying To Increase Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 10 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province wants to have 8.5 billion US dollars worth of exports
this year, compared to last year's 7.5 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The capital, Guangzhou, which accounted for a tenth of the
province's exports last year, will increase its shares of overseas
markets by keeping its current leaders like ships, pianos,
batteries, loud speakers, sewing machines for industrial use,
tires, machine tools, appliances, and telecommunications equipment.
</P>
<P>
In the near future it will increase exports of elevators,
food-processing machinery, numerally-controlled machine tools, and
fine chemicals.
</P>
<P>
In the distant future, it will focus on hi-tech products like
automobiles, tires, environmental-protection equipment, mobile
communications technology, bio-engineering, and TVs. 
