<HEADLINE> China Telecom to Develop Internet Browser </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 10 (Xinhua) -- China's largest public
telecommunications provider, China Telecom, has signed an
agreement with Microsoft Corp. to jointly develop a special
Internet browser. China Telecom expects the browser to consolidate
its leading position in the country's Internet market.
</P>
<P>
The launching of the "Internet Explorer China" project marks
the beginning of a long-term cooperative program between Microsoft
and China's Ministry of Post and Telecommunications (MPT), which
runs China Telecom, said Leng Rongquan, deputy director in charge
of the department of telecommunications of the MPT.
</P>
<P>
Subscribers to the Internet through China Telecom will receive
"IE China" free to encourage use of the company's public
multimedia telecom service.
</P>
<P>
Neither China Telecom nor Microsoft revealed financial terms.
</P>
<P>
According to the long-term agreement, China Telecom will also
use Microsoft platforms and other technology in information system
applications. Microsoft will be involved in the training for
online skills.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the MPT show China had 620,000 subscribers to
the Internet at the end of 1997.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
