<HEADLINE> 9 Killed, 35 Injured in Bomb Blast in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 10 (Xinhua) -- At least nine people were
killed and 35 others injured Tuesday morning when a bomb went off
in a passenger train in Pakistan's eastern province of Punjab.
</P>
<P>
The explosion took place at 7:25 a.m. (local time). The train
was heading for Kasur, about 50 kilometers southeast of the
provincial capital of Lahore, the Associated Press of Pakistan
said.
</P>
<P>
This was the second train blast in the past two days in the
province. A blast occurred Monday afternoon on a running train
near a small town named Wan Adhan, about 56 kilometers southwest
of Lahore, killing five people and injuring 35 others.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, one person was killed and 12 others injured Monday
morning in a bomb explosion in Pakistan's southwestern province of
Balochistan. 
</P>
