<HEADLINE> 23 People Feared Killed in Road Accident in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-three people were feared
drowned Monday evening when a wagon fell into a river in northern
Pakistan, local newspapers reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The wagon carrying 26 people, who were going to attend a
wedding ceremony of their relatives, fell into a deep ravine near
Ramgotpari, about 50 kilometers from Gilgit, a major city in
northern Pakistan, according to the reports.
</P>
<P>
