<HEADLINE> Huge Handwritten Copy of Selected Works of Deng Xiaoping Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 10 (Xinhua) -- A retired cadre in northwest
China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region has finished a 418-page
handwritten copy of the "Volume III of Selected Works of Deng
Xiaoping" with 50 writing brushes.
</P>
<P>
Today's Guangming Daily reported that the 10-kilogram
handwritten copy took Cheng Dechun 2 and a half years to complete.
</P>
<P>
Cheng copied down one or two pages from Deng's book each day
since his retirement in May of 1995.
</P>
<P>
To copy 288,000 Chinese characters, 50 writing brushes were
used up.
</P>
<P>
The purple cover of the copied book is 93 centimeters long and
62 centimeters wide.
</P>
<P>
Calligraphy experts said Cheng's copy is rarely seen in terms
of its volume and weight.  
</P>
</TEXT>
