<HEADLINE> Thailand Steps Up Tourism Promotion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 10 (Xinhua) -- The Economic Policy Committee of
Thailand has called for support from government agencies to
tourism in a bid to secure the revenue from the industry, the
Bangkok Post newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The committee urged short- and long-term measures to upgrade
destinations, improve attractions, promote the Amazing Thailand
campaign and train personnel.
</P>
<P>
It on Monday ordered government agencies to extend support to
the tourism industry, which is one of the country's top
foreign-exchange earning industries.
</P>
<P>
Additional measures are sought to improve tourists' security,
crack down on rip-offs, improve destinations, develop shopping
areas and promote special-interest travel.
</P>
<P>
Tourists' security is among the top priorities after a Canadian
visitor was murdered on Ko Samet while an Israeli tourist was
raped in Chiang Mai.
</P>
<P>
A coordinating center for tourists security will be set up by
the Interior Ministry, which also pledged to properly regulate
water sports and vehicles related to tourism.
</P>
<P>
Measures will also be taken to develop shopping streets aiming
to encourage more visitor spending and to promote special-interest
travel, such as diving, Thai cuisine, traditional massage and
cultural heritage.
</P>
<P>
The government also plans to take four long-term measures for
improving tourist sites, the industry's staff and facility and the
convention and exhibition market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
