<HEADLINE> China Issues Temporary Provisions on Transient Children's Schooling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 10 (Xinhua) -- A temporary provision has been
issued jointly by China's National Education Commission (NEC) and
the Ministry of Public Security (MPS) to ensure that all transient
children attend school.
</P>
<P>
Officials believe that in many of China's coastal areas and
large cities, more transient laborers are bringing their families
with them. This increases the number of transient children and
creates a problem for the government in providing schools.
</P>
<P>
In a circulation released today, both the NEC and the MPS urged
related departments to take active measures to create more
educational opportunities for transient children.
</P>
<P>
According to the temporary provision, the main channel for
transient children's schooling is to go to local full-time public
schools.
</P>
<P>
The provision also calls for the establishment of special
private schools for transient children. 
</P>
