<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Emporium Sells Gems Worth US$3 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, March 10 (Xinhua) -- A total of 3.15 million U.S.
dollars' worth of gems, jade, pearl and jewelry were sold at the
six-day annual Myanmar Gems Emporium which ended here Monday, The
New Light of Myanmar official newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The emporium attracted 239 merchants of 161 companies from
seven countries or regions, including Japan, Thailand, China and
China's Hong Kong Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
It also drew 136 gems traders from 59 local companies.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar, a well-known producer of jade, ruby and sapphire in
the world, has held gems emporiums annually since 1964 with
additional mid-year ones introduced in the past six years.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar earned more than 260 million dollars from the 35 annual
and six mid-year gems emporiums.  
</P>
</TEXT>
