<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1st Fresh-Water Well Dug in Lop Nur </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese geologists have recently
succeeded in digging a fresh-water well in the Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region's Lop Nur area.
</P>
<P>
This is the first fresh water well in this so-called "dry pole"
of the world.
</P>
<P>
The 465-m-deep well produces 452.5 cubic meters of water daily.
</P>
<P>
Since last June, a team from the Regional Geological Inspection
Bureau has gone to the Lop Nur 11 times to work.
</P>
<P>
The Lop Nur was a lake in the past, surrounded by forests and
grassland. Since 1972, it has been a dry and barren landscape, and
many scientists and explorers gave their lives because of the lack
of water, while working there.
</P>
<P>
The authorities concerned have decided to set up a transfer
station where the well is located, with houses and trees and grass
to protect travelers from the sun. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
