<HEADLINE> Agassi Beats Woodbridge in Champions Cup Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 9 (inhua) -- American Andre Agassi, fresh
from his second tournament win of the year, beat Australian Todd
Woodbridge in two tight sets Monday to reach the second round of
the 2.45 million U.S. dollars Champions Cup tennis tournament in
Indian Wells, California.
</P>
<P>
Agassi knocked out the Australian, ranking 34th in the world,
7-6 (7-3), 6-4. The American stretched his winning streak to 11
matches, during which he has dropped only one set.
</P>
<P>
The top eight seeds, led by world No. 1 American Pete Sampras,
have first-round byes in the tournament, the first of the
prestigious Super Nine events of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Nicolas Kiefer edged French Open champion Gustavo
Kuerten, the 10th seed, 6-4, 6-7 (4-7), 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Ninth-seeded Spaniard Alex Corretja lost to Sweden's Magnus
Norman 7-5, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Spain's Albert Costa ousted 13th-seeded compatriot Felix
Mantilla, 4-6, 6-4, 6-3, while 11th-seeded Slovakian Karol Kucera
defeated his compatriot Dominik Hrbaty 6-4, 1-6, 7-6 (7-5) and
14th seed Sergi Bruguera of Spain defeated compatriot Julian
Alonso 7-6 (7-0), 6-3. 
</P>
