<HEADLINE> Romanian FM: Kosovo Crisis May Threat Balkan Stability </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, March 9 (Xinhua) -- The Kosovo crisis will be a
threat to stability in the Balkan region if it is not resolved
promptly, warned Romanian Foreign Minister Andrei Plesu on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Plesu was speaking after a one-day visit to Bulgaria where the
conflict in Kosovo topped the agenda.
</P>
<P>
Violence broke out earlier this month when Serbian police
clashed with the ethnic Albanian majority who have been seeking
independence from Yugoslavia since 1981.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, Romania, Bulgaria, Greece and Turkey issued a joint
statement on Kosovo calling for diplomatic means to resolve the
crisis.
</P>
<P>
The statement condemned terrorism and urged that both the
rights of ethnic Albanians in Kosovo and the sovereignty of
Yugoslavia be respected.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Romanian Foreign Ministry stressed the
statement did not mention international military intervention,
adding that Romania will encourage more countries to sign the
statement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
