<HEADLINE> Poland, Germany, Denmark Start Naval Exercise in Baltic Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, March 9 (Xinhua) -- Poland, Germany and Denmark began a
four-day joint naval exercise in the Baltic Sea on Monday, a
Polish navy spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Janus Zwalczak said that three Polish missile destroyers will
participate in the wargame in the south Baltic and within the
German territorial waters.
</P>
<P>
The maneuver will practice salvaging wrecked ships and rescuing
wounded personnel.
</P>
<P>
Poland, which has been accepted for NATO membership, is active
in joint military exercises with NATO countries.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, Warsaw will send an ambulance ship to
Portugal, where 14 navy ships from France, Spain, Portugal and
Sweden will also practice salvage. 
</P>
