<HEADLINE> hke031002 -Soeharto Renominated Candidate for Indonesian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 10 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's People's Consultative
Assembly (MPR) Tuesday formally announced that it has renominated
incumbent President Soeharto for candidate of president for the
1998-2003 term.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made by the MPR at the beginning of
Tuesday's session. The MPR started its General Session on March 1.
</P>
<P>
The five-yearly session, which will end on Wednesday, is being
attended by 1,000 members of the country's highest state
institution. The session will endorse the State policy Guidelines
for the next five years and elect a president and vice-president
of the state.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto, 76, in office since 1966, was re-elected in March
1993 for the sixth five-year term.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto agreed on Sunday to be nominated for a seventh
five-year term.
</P>
<P>
"The president humbly asked if this is the people's
aspirations, he is prepared to serve the county and people,"
military delegation chief Lieutenant General Yunus Yosfiah said
after a meeting with the president.
</P>
<P>
After the announcement, the MPR will soon elect the president
by an oral vote.  
</P>
</TEXT>
