<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese City Protecting Old Official Residential Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, March 10 (Xinhua) -- The authorities of Nanjing, the
capital of east China's Jiangsu Province, plans to take steps to
protect the old residential area where high-ranking government
officials lived before 1949.
</P>
<P>
The Kuomintang government, which ruled China from 1911-1949,
had a program called the Capital Program to build Nanjing, then
the nation's capital. Many famous Chinese architects were involved
in the urban planning and construction scheme in the 1920s and
1930s.
</P>
<P>
The current program is designed to protect the old style of the
streets in that area and any buildings and houses that were built
later and are not in the traditional architectural style will be
torn down. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980310.0306 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-10 </DATE_TIME>
