<HEADLINE> Top Chinese Badminton Player Withdraws from All-England </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 10 (Xinhua) -- China's top men's player and
defending champion Dong Jiong has pulled out of the All-England
badminton championships which start Tuesday, Chinese head coach Li
Yongbo confirmed Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
Dong, ranked third in the world, opted out of the championships
after injuring his right knee in training, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Instead, Dong will concentrate on the Thomas Cup team finals to
be held in Hong Kong in May, the Chinese coach said.
</P>
<P>
His non-appearance came after world champion Peter Rasmussen of
Denmark pulled out with an ankle injury the day before. 
</P>
