<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China Province Helps Handicapped </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 10 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province has
found ways to help its handicapped citizens take part in social
activities and enjoy a normal life.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the Board of the Provincial Federation of the
Handicapped Cai Yuanting explained its methods at a recent news
conference in Fuzhou, the capital.
</P>
<P>
Fujian has 1.61 million people with mental or physical
handicaps, accounting for 4.76 percent of the province's
population.
</P>
<P>
To assist the handicapped, the local government has established
some 300 grassroots stations and 70 special schools for them, and
in recent years, 24,000 cataract patients, nearly 4,000 deaf
children, and more than 7,000 polio patients have gotten help
through government programs.
</P>
<P>
The government has also provided at least 10 million yuan in
special funds to help poverty-stricken handicapped people.
</P>
<P>
However, there are still 150,000 handicapped people in Fujian
living with poverty, and nearly 35 percent of school-aged retarded
children in the province are out of school, while 30 percent of
adults with handicaps are jobless, according to official
figures.
</P>
<P>
Eleven provincial government departments recently held their
annual campaign to increase support for people with
handicaps. 
</P>
</TEXT>
