<HEADLINE> IDB Backs Integrated Financial Management System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 9 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank (IDB) announced Monday the approval of an 11.05 million U.S.
dollar financing for the Dominican Republic for the setting up of
an integrated financial management system.
</P>
<P>
The project is designed to improve the management of government
assets and liabilities as well as increase administrative
transparency and effectiveness of internal controls.
</P>
<P>
The project will finance consulting services, training and
equipment for designing and introducing the integrated financial
management system with a set of standards that will be designed,
developed and established. Computer linkages will be set up for
the government's core fiscal management units and systems.
</P>
